import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    x_ticks = plt.xticks()[0]
    if len(x_ticks) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    division_counts = data['division'].value_counts()
    division_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    home_wins = len(data[data['score_difference'] > 0])
    away_wins = len(data[data['score_difference'] < 0])
    labels = ['Home Team Wins', 'Away Team Wins']
    sizes = [home_wins, away_wins]
    
    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home team wins vs away team wins?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
